1
00:01:27,360 --> 00:01:34,320
=Hold a Court Now=

2
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:38,000
=Episode 17=

3
00:01:51,640 --> 00:01:53,440
Want me to give you a lift?

4
00:01:54,230 --> 00:01:55,110
No, thanks.

5
00:01:55,750 --> 00:01:56,830
I'm meeting a client.

6
00:01:57,800 --> 00:01:58,920
I'm actually running late.

7
00:01:59,560 --> 00:02:01,280
I'll drop off your grandma's cured meat

8
00:02:02,080 --> 00:02:03,230
at your place tomorrow.

9
00:02:04,030 --> 00:02:05,230
Just keep it for yourself.

10
00:02:05,830 --> 00:02:07,280
Grandma meant for you to have it.

11
00:02:12,160 --> 00:02:13,600
Don't use too much salt
when you cook it.

12
00:02:29,910 --> 00:02:31,190
(Heavenly Goddess,)

13
00:02:31,910 --> 00:02:34,280
(when I broke my leg at six years old,)

14
00:02:34,280 --> 00:02:36,680
(I prayed for things to go my way.)

15
00:02:36,680 --> 00:02:39,160
(I asked for a divine warrior
to come save me.)

16
00:02:39,750 --> 00:02:41,000
(And then,)

17
00:02:41,510 --> 00:02:42,840
(over twenty years later,)

18
00:02:43,160 --> 00:02:45,240
(you sent me Machine Shen?)

19
00:02:46,070 --> 00:02:48,560
(A Machine Shen bound
by conflict-of-interest rules, no less.)

20
00:02:59,070 --> 00:03:00,280
Hey, you scared me!

21
00:03:00,280 --> 00:03:01,720
How long have you been there?

22
00:03:02,280 --> 00:03:03,280
I said hello to you

23
00:03:03,280 --> 00:03:04,880
the second you walked in.

24
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,470
You did?

25
00:03:06,470 --> 00:03:07,510
When you got back,

26
00:03:07,510 --> 00:03:09,070
I asked why you were home so early.

27
00:03:09,190 --> 00:03:10,000
You said you took

28
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:11,310
a taxi straight from the airport.

29
00:03:16,120 --> 00:03:17,350
You're way too young

30
00:03:17,840 --> 00:03:19,030
to be having memory loss.

31
00:03:20,440 --> 00:03:21,560
At this rate,

32
00:03:21,560 --> 00:03:23,470
I'll be the one
looking after you in your old age.

33
00:03:29,470 --> 00:03:30,790
Aren't you playing ball today?

34
00:03:31,440 --> 00:03:34,280
I was supposed
to play one-on-one with Mr. Xu,

35
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:36,000
but of all things,

36
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:37,720
he had to go and sprain his ankle.

37
00:03:38,600 --> 00:03:39,440
I think he chickened out,

38
00:03:39,440 --> 00:03:40,910
but he wouldn't admit it.

39
00:03:43,310 --> 00:03:44,910
Since I was already out,

40
00:03:45,240 --> 00:03:46,310
I figured I'd stay out.

41
00:03:47,790 --> 00:03:49,120
So, I came here to kill some time.

42
00:03:49,350 --> 00:03:50,470
Am I bothering you?

43
00:03:50,510 --> 00:03:51,510
Yes.

44
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:52,630
Fine.

45
00:03:53,440 --> 00:03:54,400
I'm leaving.

46
00:03:55,590 --> 00:03:56,910
Remember, you're kicking me out.

47
00:03:57,070 --> 00:03:58,470
Don't call me irresponsible.

48
00:03:59,590 --> 00:04:00,840
Do you even have anywhere to go?

49
00:04:01,470 --> 00:04:02,910
I'll find a random game at the court.

50
00:04:03,470 --> 00:04:04,840
If your sister-in-law calls...

51
00:04:05,310 --> 00:04:05,680
Just...

52
00:04:05,680 --> 00:04:08,000
I'll tell her
you're closing a big deal.

53
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:09,000
A billion-yuan deal.

54
00:04:09,440 --> 00:04:10,440
Let's not exaggerate.

55
00:04:10,750 --> 00:04:11,910
Keep it realistic.

56
00:04:12,070 --> 00:04:13,000
But you know,

57
00:04:13,030 --> 00:04:14,560
you can find leads at the court.

58
00:04:14,750 --> 00:04:16,150
That guy who pulled an arm?

59
00:04:16,480 --> 00:04:17,630
His case is still ongoing.

60
00:04:17,710 --> 00:04:19,440
Too bad Old Li beat me to it.

61
00:04:23,310 --> 00:04:25,310
Did you pack my heart pills?

62
00:04:28,950 --> 00:04:29,950
Here, take these.

63
00:04:30,680 --> 00:04:32,070
They're specialties from back home.

64
00:04:32,190 --> 00:04:33,070
Take some.

65
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:34,510
In case your blood sugar drops,

66
00:04:34,710 --> 00:04:35,950
you can have one right away.

67
00:04:37,680 --> 00:04:38,510
Thanks.

68
00:04:45,600 --> 00:04:47,680
Take it easy on the court.
Don't go spraining an ankle.

69
00:04:50,630 --> 00:04:52,120
Always so exasperating.

70
00:04:58,800 --> 00:04:59,680
Dried chrysanthemums...

71
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:01,680
Sausages...

72
00:05:04,750 --> 00:05:06,880
Why'd you buy so much local stuff?

73
00:05:06,880 --> 00:05:08,880
None of these even has labels.

74
00:05:09,270 --> 00:05:10,440
What do you mean "no labels"?

75
00:05:10,480 --> 00:05:12,070
I bought them at a farmer's market.

76
00:05:12,800 --> 00:05:13,920
Fine.

77
00:05:18,950 --> 00:05:20,830
Since when do you eat candy?

78
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:22,240
You've never had a sweet tooth.

79
00:05:24,120 --> 00:05:25,480
Not mine. I grabbed the wrong bag.

80
00:05:25,630 --> 00:05:26,600
Then whose is it?

81
00:05:27,830 --> 00:05:29,070
Who was with you

82
00:05:29,710 --> 00:05:30,880
on this business trip?

83
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:33,440
I told you already.

84
00:05:33,440 --> 00:05:34,830
I went alone.

85
00:05:36,150 --> 00:05:38,920
Well, a local court clerk helped out.

86
00:05:39,270 --> 00:05:41,920
I just saw the villagers at the market

87
00:05:41,920 --> 00:05:43,880
and picked up a few gifts on a whim.

88
00:05:43,880 --> 00:05:45,120
Some are for my colleagues too.

89
00:05:45,120 --> 00:05:45,950
You?

90
00:05:46,360 --> 00:05:47,750
Buying gifts for colleagues?

91
00:05:48,630 --> 00:05:49,800
Don't try to fool me.

92
00:05:49,950 --> 00:05:51,070
I'm your mother.

93
00:05:55,830 --> 00:05:57,390
What reason would I have to lie?

94
00:05:58,070 --> 00:05:58,880
Please.

95
00:05:59,120 --> 00:06:00,120
The over-explaining

96
00:06:00,120 --> 00:06:01,920
tells me you have something to hide.

97
00:06:02,390 --> 00:06:03,800
But I'll stop asking.

98
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:05,270
I'll just wait for you

99
00:06:05,270 --> 00:06:06,510
to slip up on your own.

100
00:06:06,510 --> 00:06:07,070
Right.

101
00:06:07,070 --> 00:06:08,630
I'll cook these for dinner tonight.

102
00:06:10,390 --> 00:06:12,310
I'm not staying.
I have to head out soon.

103
00:06:16,680 --> 00:06:18,070
Your skewers are ready.

104
00:06:19,040 --> 00:06:20,000
I tweaked

105
00:06:20,240 --> 00:06:21,480
the sauce a little.

106
00:06:21,680 --> 00:06:22,630
Give me some feedback.

107
00:06:22,630 --> 00:06:23,600
Try it.

108
00:06:26,150 --> 00:06:27,480
The girls need to talk.

109
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:29,800
About your job?

110
00:06:29,830 --> 00:06:31,390
Got it. Protocol first.

111
00:06:31,390 --> 00:06:32,710
I'm recusing myself.

112
00:06:32,950 --> 00:06:33,830
Enjoy your food.

113
00:06:33,830 --> 00:06:34,830
Thanks, Yongjiu.

114
00:06:38,830 --> 00:06:40,120
This drawing is incredible.

115
00:06:44,270 --> 00:06:46,390
This baby definitely likes bold flavors.

116
00:06:46,560 --> 00:06:48,360
Stop calling it a "baby."

117
00:06:48,360 --> 00:06:49,240
To me,

118
00:06:49,240 --> 00:06:50,710
it's still just a fertilized egg.

119
00:06:50,710 --> 00:06:52,440
Thinking of it that way
is too much pressure.

120
00:06:53,830 --> 00:06:55,750
Look, if you genuinely
didn't want kids,

121
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:57,310
I wouldn't say a word.

122
00:06:57,600 --> 00:06:59,750
But you clearly love kids.

123
00:07:00,190 --> 00:07:01,560
You're just too hard on yourself.

124
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:03,000
You want everything to be perfect.

125
00:07:03,560 --> 00:07:05,560
We can't control

126
00:07:05,680 --> 00:07:07,070
if they'll even be successful.

127
00:07:07,240 --> 00:07:10,400
But giving the child a home full of love

128
00:07:10,400 --> 00:07:11,630
is entirely up to us.

129
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:14,440
And you and Xiao Bing?

130
00:07:14,440 --> 00:07:16,040
You're the gold standard for couples.

131
00:07:16,040 --> 00:07:18,000
You'll give that child
100% of your heart.

132
00:07:18,560 --> 00:07:19,750
There's nothing to worry about.

133
00:07:20,150 --> 00:07:21,060
But as judges,

134
00:07:21,060 --> 00:07:22,920
we see the worst-case scenarios.

135
00:07:23,950 --> 00:07:25,510
It makes me over-analyze everything.

136
00:07:25,510 --> 00:07:27,470
I worry that if I mess up
even one step,

137
00:07:27,480 --> 00:07:29,030
I'm the one failing the child.

138
00:07:29,950 --> 00:07:31,440
Don't get inside your own head.

139
00:07:31,750 --> 00:07:34,240
It's obvious Xiao Bing is
going to be a softie.

140
00:07:35,920 --> 00:07:37,360
He claims he doesn't mind

141
00:07:37,360 --> 00:07:38,710
and will follow my lead,

142
00:07:38,950 --> 00:07:40,120
but in reality,

143
00:07:40,410 --> 00:07:41,800
he's read every parenting book

144
00:07:41,880 --> 00:07:43,330
cover to cover.

145
00:07:43,330 --> 00:07:44,810
He's even started

146
00:07:44,810 --> 00:07:46,240
planning the nursery.

147
00:07:47,560 --> 00:07:49,710
That just shows how much
he values you and the baby.

148
00:07:50,340 --> 00:07:51,950
He's going to be a great father.

149
00:07:53,190 --> 00:07:54,560
If you think of a person's life,

150
00:07:54,560 --> 00:07:56,920
from start to finish,

151
00:07:56,920 --> 00:07:58,800
as Version 1.0...

152
00:07:59,190 --> 00:08:00,630
then parenthood

153
00:08:01,040 --> 00:08:03,440
is like Version 2.0.

154
00:08:03,440 --> 00:08:04,310
Because

155
00:08:04,310 --> 00:08:07,040
it gives you a chance
to re-examine your own childhood.

156
00:08:07,560 --> 00:08:09,240
You get a second chance

157
00:08:09,390 --> 00:08:11,240
to make up for all the regrets

158
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:12,390
you had while growing up.

159
00:08:13,070 --> 00:08:15,360
If you're lucky enough
to have grandkids,

160
00:08:15,830 --> 00:08:16,950
that's when

161
00:08:17,390 --> 00:08:18,920
you get to fix the mistakes

162
00:08:18,920 --> 00:08:20,800
you made while raising your own kids

163
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:22,120
in your middle age.

164
00:08:22,120 --> 00:08:24,510
So, basically an upgrade to Version 3.0?

165
00:08:27,750 --> 00:08:28,560
Jing,

166
00:08:28,560 --> 00:08:30,150
do you think I'm just being selfish?

167
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:33,390
Don't mind my rambling.

168
00:08:33,670 --> 00:08:34,630
The truth is,

169
00:08:34,630 --> 00:08:37,080
everyone is handed
a different script in life.

170
00:08:37,550 --> 00:08:38,720
But having children

171
00:08:39,030 --> 00:08:40,720
isn't just about pressure and duty.

172
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:42,630
It's a life experience

173
00:08:42,790 --> 00:08:44,750
that simply can't be replaced

174
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:46,670
by anything else.

175
00:08:47,270 --> 00:08:48,720
A child is the glue

176
00:08:48,880 --> 00:08:51,030
that holds a marriage together.

177
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:53,670
For the grandparents,
they're an elixir of youth.

178
00:08:55,200 --> 00:08:56,320
Think about it.

179
00:08:56,720 --> 00:08:58,390
Just seeing Fei sitting there,

180
00:08:58,630 --> 00:08:59,880
perfectly still.

181
00:09:00,240 --> 00:09:01,550
She looks so tiny.

182
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:03,270
My whole world

183
00:09:03,360 --> 00:09:05,210
just lights up instantly.

184
00:09:06,630 --> 00:09:08,960
Is it a total loss of humanity,

185
00:09:09,120 --> 00:09:10,880
or a complete moral collapse?

186
00:09:11,200 --> 00:09:12,150
Let's find out together.

187
00:09:12,150 --> 00:09:13,480
You don't want to miss this.

188
00:09:13,480 --> 00:09:14,720
Follow Rui's Legal Lens.

189
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:15,960
That's all for today's segment

190
00:09:15,960 --> 00:09:17,430
on AI-generated rumors targeting women.

191
00:09:17,430 --> 00:09:18,320
In our next episode,

192
00:09:18,320 --> 00:09:20,000
I'll be covering

193
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:22,080
hidden cameras in female locker rooms,

194
00:09:22,080 --> 00:09:24,720
investigations into
gender-biased hiring,

195
00:09:24,720 --> 00:09:27,030
and victims of online dating scams.

196
00:09:27,030 --> 00:09:29,430
As my followers already know,

197
00:09:29,430 --> 00:09:31,150
the details of the investigation

198
00:09:31,150 --> 00:09:31,790
or the specific

199
00:09:31,790 --> 00:09:33,390
sentences the criminals receive

200
00:09:33,510 --> 00:09:35,430
aren't the main focus here
at Rui's Legal Lens.

201
00:09:35,840 --> 00:09:37,750
We care more about women's safety

202
00:09:37,750 --> 00:09:39,630
and protecting their fundamental rights.

203
00:09:53,550 --> 00:09:54,430
Alright.

204
00:09:55,120 --> 00:09:57,030
Lian is calling me for dinner,

205
00:09:57,030 --> 00:09:58,550
so that's it for today's show.

206
00:09:58,720 --> 00:09:59,550
Don't forget to

207
00:09:59,670 --> 00:10:01,120
like, save,

208
00:10:01,910 --> 00:10:03,000
and follow Rui's Legal Lens.

209
00:10:15,030 --> 00:10:15,720
Hello.

210
00:10:15,880 --> 00:10:16,880
Hello.

211
00:10:17,430 --> 00:10:18,600
Are you guys closed yet?

212
00:10:19,880 --> 00:10:21,880
Not yet. Please, come in.

213
00:10:23,600 --> 00:10:24,630
Thank you.

214
00:10:24,630 --> 00:10:25,790
Oh, you're injured.

215
00:10:25,910 --> 00:10:26,550
Yes.

216
00:10:26,550 --> 00:10:27,910
It looks pretty serious.

217
00:10:27,910 --> 00:10:29,150
I'm okay. I can manage.

218
00:10:29,150 --> 00:10:30,120
Take it slow.

219
00:10:33,510 --> 00:10:35,270
Have a seat. I'll get you some water.

220
00:10:35,320 --> 00:10:36,480
Thank you.

221
00:10:38,360 --> 00:10:39,360
And your name is?

222
00:10:39,960 --> 00:10:41,120
I'm Lu Huilan.

223
00:10:43,150 --> 00:10:44,080
Let me help you with that.

224
00:10:44,080 --> 00:10:45,240
Alright, thank you.

225
00:10:47,080 --> 00:10:48,240
So,

226
00:10:48,840 --> 00:10:49,840
what happened?

227
00:10:50,630 --> 00:10:52,150
I was on my e-bike,

228
00:10:52,630 --> 00:10:54,790
taking my father to the doctor,

229
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:56,480
and I hit a car.

230
00:10:56,480 --> 00:10:57,720
Who was found responsible?

231
00:10:57,750 --> 00:10:58,630
I was.

232
00:11:00,790 --> 00:11:02,510
I imagine the medical bills are high.

233
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:06,000
Over 30,000 yuan so far.

234
00:11:06,880 --> 00:11:08,360
My leg is fractured.

235
00:11:09,200 --> 00:11:10,200
The doctor says

236
00:11:11,910 --> 00:11:13,270
it isn't healing well,

237
00:11:13,270 --> 00:11:15,030
so I might need more surgery.

238
00:11:15,750 --> 00:11:17,240
And as for the driver

239
00:11:17,240 --> 00:11:18,430
and the car,

240
00:11:18,550 --> 00:11:20,150
there might be other damages.

241
00:11:20,790 --> 00:11:22,670
Were you at fault,
or was it shared liability?

242
00:11:22,750 --> 00:11:23,840
I'm fully liable.

243
00:11:24,790 --> 00:11:26,240
Are you planning to sue the police

244
00:11:26,430 --> 00:11:27,670
for a wrongful fault determination?

245
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:29,440
Did you file for an administrative review?

246
00:11:30,480 --> 00:11:31,390
No, that's not...

247
00:11:31,880 --> 00:11:32,880
Look,

248
00:11:33,150 --> 00:11:34,430
I really was 100% at fault.

249
00:11:35,360 --> 00:11:36,430
I ran a red light.

250
00:11:39,080 --> 00:11:40,910
Then, why have you come to see me?

251
00:11:42,720 --> 00:11:45,080
My two brothers are suing me.

252
00:11:46,910 --> 00:11:47,750
Wait,

253
00:11:47,960 --> 00:11:49,510
the car you hit
belonged to your brothers?

254
00:11:49,720 --> 00:11:50,550
No.

255
00:11:51,270 --> 00:11:52,600
I was on my e-bike,

256
00:11:52,720 --> 00:11:54,880
taking my father to see a doctor.

257
00:11:55,270 --> 00:11:56,150
When we crashed,

258
00:11:57,390 --> 00:11:58,600
my father died.

259
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:04,080
Now I'm facing a lawsuit.

260
00:12:04,960 --> 00:12:05,960
They want me

261
00:12:08,360 --> 00:12:09,840
to pay 300,000 yuan.

262
00:12:09,910 --> 00:12:10,880
Please,

263
00:12:11,670 --> 00:12:13,120
you have to help me.

264
00:12:14,430 --> 00:12:17,080
I really don't know what to do.

265
00:12:17,150 --> 00:12:18,480
Take a breath, Ms. Lu.

266
00:12:18,670 --> 00:12:19,750
It's not that I won't help you,

267
00:12:20,670 --> 00:12:21,720
but look at the facts.

268
00:12:21,880 --> 00:12:22,880
This is a traffic accident.

269
00:12:23,030 --> 00:12:23,960
It's crystal clear.

270
00:12:24,080 --> 00:12:25,430
A judge will see that instantly.

271
00:12:25,550 --> 00:12:27,320
The judge just needs to figure out

272
00:12:27,320 --> 00:12:28,670
how the law applies here.

273
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:30,120
Honestly, any judge

274
00:12:30,200 --> 00:12:31,430
with a shred of conscience

275
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:33,000
will reduce your liability anyway.

276
00:12:33,670 --> 00:12:35,550
You don't necessarily
even need a lawyer.

277
00:12:36,150 --> 00:12:37,390
I'd hate to see you

278
00:12:37,480 --> 00:12:38,510
waste your money here.

279
00:12:38,510 --> 00:12:40,550
But I've never been in a courtroom.

280
00:12:41,600 --> 00:12:42,670
I'm so nervous.

281
00:12:42,670 --> 00:12:44,270
What am I even supposed to say?

282
00:12:45,360 --> 00:12:47,360
Most people haven't been to court.

283
00:12:47,670 --> 00:12:48,960
It's enough to make

284
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:50,320
anyone's blood pressure spike.

285
00:12:50,360 --> 00:12:50,960
Tell you what.

286
00:12:50,960 --> 00:12:52,200
If you're really that anxious,

287
00:12:52,200 --> 00:12:52,910
feel free

288
00:12:52,910 --> 00:12:53,960
to just stop by.

289
00:12:54,030 --> 00:12:55,550
We'll have some tea together

290
00:12:56,030 --> 00:12:57,000
and calm your nerves.

291
00:12:58,390 --> 00:13:00,080
Because if you sit here any longer,

292
00:13:00,320 --> 00:13:00,840
my conscience

293
00:13:00,840 --> 00:13:02,630
won't be able to hold back my ambition.

294
00:13:02,960 --> 00:13:04,670
I'll fast-talk you
into signing a contract.

295
00:13:06,910 --> 00:13:08,080
Trust me.

296
00:13:08,320 --> 00:13:10,240
Just let the judge handle it.

297
00:13:10,600 --> 00:13:11,360
And once you leave,

298
00:13:11,360 --> 00:13:12,080
don't go running off

299
00:13:12,080 --> 00:13:13,430
to some other law firm.

300
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:20,080
It takes two to make a baby, you know.

301
00:13:20,240 --> 00:13:21,550
You should at least consider

302
00:13:21,550 --> 00:13:23,080
how Xiao Bing feels.

303
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:25,320
I know the logic.

304
00:13:25,550 --> 00:13:28,240
But it's different
when it's your own life.

305
00:13:28,910 --> 00:13:31,080
I'm just completely lost.

306
00:13:31,360 --> 00:13:33,720
You're always calling us indecisive.

307
00:13:33,790 --> 00:13:34,910
Look at you now.

308
00:13:34,910 --> 00:13:36,430
You're overthinking every little thing.

309
00:13:36,430 --> 00:13:37,550
This isn't your usual self.

310
00:13:40,840 --> 00:13:42,240
How are things with Yongjiu?

311
00:13:42,240 --> 00:13:43,510
Are you two back on track?

312
00:13:47,750 --> 00:13:48,960
Hardly.

313
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:50,980
He've been home for two hours,

314
00:13:51,150 --> 00:13:52,750
and still reeked of mutton.

315
00:13:53,020 --> 00:13:54,120
But it's okay.

316
00:13:55,120 --> 00:13:56,000
A few years ago,

317
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:58,360
he was the rising star
at the Intermediate People's Court.

318
00:13:58,600 --> 00:13:59,720
And years later,

319
00:13:59,790 --> 00:14:02,720
and he's the local legend
of grilled skewers.

320
00:14:03,880 --> 00:14:05,080
Right before you got here,

321
00:14:05,200 --> 00:14:06,670
he was unclogging a sewage pipe.

322
00:14:06,720 --> 00:14:08,510
God, the stench was unbearable.

323
00:14:08,910 --> 00:14:10,080
Shh! Keep it down.

324
00:14:12,240 --> 00:14:13,600
But back then,

325
00:14:13,600 --> 00:14:15,840
he didn't exactly have a choice
but to leave the court.

326
00:14:17,980 --> 00:14:19,310
He talks about it all the time.

327
00:14:19,520 --> 00:14:21,360
He blames himself

328
00:14:21,550 --> 00:14:22,750
for not taking care of Fei.

329
00:14:22,750 --> 00:14:24,200
Otherwise,
none of it would've happened.

330
00:14:26,750 --> 00:14:27,720
Has he considered

331
00:14:27,720 --> 00:14:29,030
returning to the legal field?

332
00:14:30,670 --> 00:14:32,030
Actually,

333
00:14:32,030 --> 00:14:33,360
we were just talking about that.

334
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:36,270
After the incident with Fei,

335
00:14:36,390 --> 00:14:37,390
she needed

336
00:14:37,390 --> 00:14:38,960
round-the-clock care.

337
00:14:39,150 --> 00:14:41,030
I offered to quit my job,

338
00:14:41,360 --> 00:14:42,600
but he wouldn't let me.

339
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:44,150
He ignored Chief Judge Feng's objections

340
00:14:44,150 --> 00:14:45,360
and handed in his resignation.

341
00:14:45,670 --> 00:14:47,030
He spent six months at home.

342
00:14:47,360 --> 00:14:49,270
Aside from speaking
to Fei for her therapy,

343
00:14:49,750 --> 00:14:51,200
he barely spoke at all.

344
00:14:52,120 --> 00:14:53,000
I know him.

345
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:54,720
Walking away from the job he loved

346
00:14:55,240 --> 00:14:56,390
and from his entire career

347
00:14:56,880 --> 00:14:58,360
is eating him alive.

348
00:15:00,200 --> 00:15:01,320
One of my seniors

349
00:15:01,320 --> 00:15:03,670
is the Legal Director
at an energy company.

350
00:15:04,150 --> 00:15:05,320
He's a fellow alum.

351
00:15:05,390 --> 00:15:06,670
He reached out the other day

352
00:15:06,670 --> 00:15:09,630
looking for a Legal Supervisor.

353
00:15:09,720 --> 00:15:10,550
They want someone

354
00:15:10,550 --> 00:15:12,240
doing the internal audits,

355
00:15:13,030 --> 00:15:14,750
specifically someone

356
00:15:14,750 --> 00:15:17,120
with experience in economic crimes.

357
00:15:17,270 --> 00:15:19,080
Could you ask Yongjiu for me?

358
00:15:19,080 --> 00:15:20,790
See if he'd be interested.

359
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:23,320
Sure. I'll bring it up when I get home.

360
00:15:23,630 --> 00:15:25,270
It's too chaotic
to have a real talk here.

361
00:15:34,510 --> 00:15:36,120
(You're afraid to look at me right now.)

362
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:39,000
(Is it because you're having)

363
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:40,120
(second thoughts about us?)

364
00:15:41,670 --> 00:15:43,120
Hi, Judge Shen.

365
00:15:43,120 --> 00:15:43,880
Remember me?

366
00:15:43,880 --> 00:15:45,430
We just saw each other this morning.

367
00:15:46,240 --> 00:15:47,200
This is for you.

368
00:15:51,360 --> 00:15:52,200
What do you think?

369
00:15:54,150 --> 00:15:56,430
I honestly believe that
when it comes to raising a child,

370
00:15:56,750 --> 00:15:58,240
money isn't the most important thing.

371
00:15:58,510 --> 00:15:59,960
They need someone who truly loves them,

372
00:15:59,960 --> 00:16:01,030
someone who's actually there

373
00:16:01,030 --> 00:16:02,390
so they can feel cherished.

374
00:16:02,790 --> 00:16:04,720
That's a gift that lasts a lifetime.

375
00:16:06,840 --> 00:16:08,750
(Take your medicine
exactly as prescribed.)

376
00:16:08,750 --> 00:16:11,560
(Once Grandma finishes this month's supply,
I'll make sure to mail the next batch.)

377
00:16:14,880 --> 00:16:15,600
Are you okay?

378
00:16:20,240 --> 00:16:26,950
♪Let me be your safe haven♪

379
00:16:28,510 --> 00:16:30,880
(I want to be the one
who takes care of you.)

380
00:16:31,320 --> 00:16:32,430
(But I'm in a dilema.)

381
00:16:33,270 --> 00:16:34,960
(I don't want us to repeat)

382
00:16:35,240 --> 00:16:37,200
(the same mistakes
as Jiang Feng and Ms. Lou.)

383
00:16:40,080 --> 00:16:42,150
(He usually looks)

384
00:16:42,550 --> 00:16:43,720
(so cold and detached,)

385
00:16:43,720 --> 00:16:46,080
(but he's surprisingly empathetic.)

386
00:16:47,480 --> 00:16:49,120
Can you send me your ID number?

387
00:16:49,270 --> 00:16:50,390
I want to sign you up

388
00:16:50,390 --> 00:16:51,960
for one of those unlimited
flight passes.

389
00:17:02,560 --> 00:17:05,890
♪ In your world ♪

390
00:17:06,200 --> 00:17:09,520
♪I want to be in your world♪

391
00:17:09,710 --> 00:17:16,010
♪I'll be there for you
until the very end♪

392
00:17:45,320 --> 00:17:47,910
How can you sleep
with your clothes on like that?

393
00:17:48,360 --> 00:17:49,520
Come on, stop being lazy.

394
00:17:49,520 --> 00:17:50,430
Get up and eat.

395
00:17:54,230 --> 00:17:55,880
Not even food can tempt you today?

396
00:17:57,120 --> 00:17:58,040
What's wrong?

397
00:17:58,800 --> 00:18:01,230
Still haven't adjusted
after getting back from home?

398
00:18:05,710 --> 00:18:07,230
Shen Xiezhi confessed
his feelings to me.

399
00:18:09,120 --> 00:18:09,910
So,

400
00:18:10,560 --> 00:18:11,630
what did you say?

401
00:18:17,470 --> 00:18:18,910
What else could I say?

402
00:18:20,230 --> 00:18:21,230
I turned him down.

403
00:18:24,630 --> 00:18:25,840
Impressive.

404
00:18:26,520 --> 00:18:27,710
What's so impressive about it?

405
00:18:28,230 --> 00:18:29,470
I'm brilliant

406
00:18:29,560 --> 00:18:30,630
with a bright future ahead.

407
00:18:31,040 --> 00:18:31,670
I'm going to be

408
00:18:31,670 --> 00:18:33,600
a top-tier lawyer at a top-tier law firm.

409
00:18:34,760 --> 00:18:35,910
In my position,

410
00:18:36,320 --> 00:18:37,390
do I really have a choice?

411
00:18:37,950 --> 00:18:39,950
Am I supposed to
throw my career away for him?

412
00:18:41,840 --> 00:18:42,840
I get it.

413
00:18:43,320 --> 00:18:44,880
So you're basically

414
00:18:44,880 --> 00:18:47,280
married to your career.

415
00:18:49,230 --> 00:18:50,470
In that case,

416
00:18:51,430 --> 00:18:53,280
just don't come crying to me in regrets

417
00:18:53,520 --> 00:18:55,360
when you're old and alone.

418
00:19:07,280 --> 00:19:08,390
Smells amazing.

419
00:19:08,520 --> 00:19:09,560
What is that?

420
00:19:11,230 --> 00:19:12,600
See? I told you

421
00:19:12,840 --> 00:19:14,150
I brought back something good.

422
00:19:14,150 --> 00:19:16,190
Since you won't get up, fine.

423
00:19:17,040 --> 00:19:17,880
You can eat in bed.

424
00:19:17,880 --> 00:19:19,430
Happy now, my lady?

425
00:19:19,430 --> 00:19:20,360
Hurry up.

426
00:19:21,040 --> 00:19:22,230
You'll feel better once you eat.

427
00:19:23,230 --> 00:19:24,470
You're the best.

428
00:19:28,520 --> 00:19:29,760
Exactly.

429
00:19:29,760 --> 00:19:31,150
How could I possibly end up alone

430
00:19:32,190 --> 00:19:33,230
with you around?

431
00:19:34,760 --> 00:19:35,880
Think about it.

432
00:19:36,190 --> 00:19:37,560
If you're turning down

433
00:19:37,630 --> 00:19:39,670
a guy like Shen Xiezhi now,

434
00:19:39,670 --> 00:19:40,670
what's going to happen

435
00:19:40,670 --> 00:19:42,840
once you're at the top
of the food chain?

436
00:19:43,760 --> 00:19:44,990
Who'll be good enough for you then?

437
00:19:45,040 --> 00:19:46,320
When I'm at the top,

438
00:19:46,320 --> 00:19:47,880
I won't need to look up.

439
00:19:47,880 --> 00:19:48,910
There'll be plenty of fish

440
00:19:49,230 --> 00:19:50,150
in the sea below me.

441
00:19:51,230 --> 00:19:52,080
Do you think

442
00:19:52,080 --> 00:19:53,520
Shen Xiezhi is going to wait around

443
00:19:53,520 --> 00:19:54,800
pining for you, do you?

444
00:19:55,990 --> 00:19:58,040
I'll just find someone else then.

445
00:19:58,710 --> 00:19:59,630
Seriously?

446
00:20:00,040 --> 00:20:01,120
Why not?

447
00:20:03,520 --> 00:20:06,150
I don't even
recognize you anymore, Qin Rui.

448
00:20:06,150 --> 00:20:06,670
What?

449
00:20:06,670 --> 00:20:08,390
Now you're talking back?

450
00:20:08,950 --> 00:20:11,360
You're clearly crazy about him,

451
00:20:11,560 --> 00:20:13,230
yet you still said no.

452
00:20:14,840 --> 00:20:17,080
Let me guess what's actually going on.

453
00:20:18,230 --> 00:20:19,390
Stop guessing.

454
00:20:19,390 --> 00:20:20,600
You're just hungry.

455
00:20:23,320 --> 00:20:24,800
Just go. I want to sleep.

456
00:20:26,470 --> 00:20:27,430
I've got it.

457
00:20:28,470 --> 00:20:30,230
There's only one logical explanation.

458
00:20:30,320 --> 00:20:32,630
He's a judge and you're a lawyer.

459
00:20:32,630 --> 00:20:34,800
Conflict-of-interest rules mean

460
00:20:34,910 --> 00:20:35,670
you can't practice

461
00:20:35,670 --> 00:20:37,710
in the same jurisdiction.

462
00:20:38,390 --> 00:20:40,560
He's at a lower court for now,

463
00:20:40,880 --> 00:20:42,560
so you could just switch districts.

464
00:20:42,560 --> 00:20:44,710
But if he ever makes it

465
00:20:45,230 --> 00:20:47,800
to the High Court,
or even the Supreme Court,

466
00:20:47,950 --> 00:20:50,760
you'll end up just like Lou Yue.

467
00:20:51,190 --> 00:20:52,320
Shut up.

468
00:20:54,230 --> 00:20:55,190
I'm telling you,

469
00:20:55,320 --> 00:20:56,760
I am not walking away from my career.

470
00:21:07,600 --> 00:21:08,600
It's alright.

471
00:21:08,990 --> 00:21:09,990
You got a lecture

472
00:21:09,990 --> 00:21:11,320
and a rejection.

473
00:21:11,320 --> 00:21:12,320
Look at me.

474
00:21:12,630 --> 00:21:13,430
I've been through it.

475
00:21:13,710 --> 00:21:14,880
But I'm still alive.

476
00:21:18,840 --> 00:21:20,230
We are nothing alike.

477
00:21:24,080 --> 00:21:25,320
I've been thinking about it.

478
00:21:26,710 --> 00:21:28,320
Qin Rui isn't actually wrong.

479
00:21:28,430 --> 00:21:30,520
She's just not the type of person

480
00:21:30,520 --> 00:21:31,800
to choose love over her career.

481
00:21:32,190 --> 00:21:33,230
I blame myself.

482
00:21:33,600 --> 00:21:34,520
I couldn't help myself,

483
00:21:35,080 --> 00:21:36,230
I've made it awkward for her.

484
00:21:40,150 --> 00:21:41,390
I get it,

485
00:21:41,430 --> 00:21:43,560
but since you two have hit the brakes

486
00:21:43,630 --> 00:21:45,760
and there's no future there anyway,

487
00:21:46,040 --> 00:21:47,230
I've got some news

488
00:21:48,320 --> 00:21:50,150
that might help you snap out of it.

489
00:21:51,710 --> 00:21:52,670
The High Court

490
00:21:52,670 --> 00:21:53,800
just posted a notice

491
00:21:53,800 --> 00:21:55,320
for a lateral transfer.

492
00:21:56,560 --> 00:21:57,880
Three openings in the criminal division.

493
00:21:59,710 --> 00:22:01,670
It's open to the entire city.

494
00:22:02,080 --> 00:22:03,710
If you're qualified, you can apply.

495
00:22:04,120 --> 00:22:05,560
Competition will be a bloodbath,

496
00:22:06,040 --> 00:22:06,910
but I think

497
00:22:06,910 --> 00:22:08,120
you've got a real shot at it.

498
00:22:10,910 --> 00:22:11,840
What?

499
00:22:12,080 --> 00:22:13,840
Why are you hesitating
on a chance like this?

500
00:22:18,320 --> 00:22:19,390
I just don't know

501
00:22:19,470 --> 00:22:21,080
if my odds are that great.

502
00:22:21,080 --> 00:22:22,360
Stop overthinking it.

503
00:22:22,470 --> 00:22:23,320
Your love life is dead,

504
00:22:23,320 --> 00:22:24,990
so you might as well
go all in on your career.

505
00:22:29,760 --> 00:22:33,360
That old scoundrel is playing my mother.
He's in his forties. My mom's over sixty.

506
00:22:33,360 --> 00:22:34,710
He's a year younger than I am!

507
00:22:34,950 --> 00:22:36,320
Plus, my mom's health is failing.

508
00:22:36,710 --> 00:22:37,950
What could he possibly want?

509
00:22:38,080 --> 00:22:38,910
Money.

510
00:22:38,910 --> 00:22:39,630
What else can it be?

511
00:22:39,630 --> 00:22:41,230
It's plain as day.

512
00:22:41,360 --> 00:22:42,430
But middle-aged women

513
00:22:42,600 --> 00:22:43,560
always fall for that act.

514
00:22:44,470 --> 00:22:45,910
He's what people call

515
00:22:46,430 --> 00:22:47,430
a real ladies' man.

516
00:22:48,710 --> 00:22:49,560
Actually,

517
00:22:49,560 --> 00:22:50,120
is our judge

518
00:22:50,120 --> 00:22:51,990
a man or a woman?

519
00:22:52,040 --> 00:22:53,840
If it's a middle-aged woman,

520
00:22:53,990 --> 00:22:55,230
he might get her

521
00:22:55,560 --> 00:22:56,710
with his smooth talk.

522
00:22:56,910 --> 00:22:57,990
That would be a disaster.

523
00:22:58,040 --> 00:22:59,190
That's impossible.

524
00:22:59,600 --> 00:23:01,880
The guy can't be that charming.

525
00:23:03,150 --> 00:23:04,800
I'm not sure which judge

526
00:23:04,800 --> 00:23:05,880
we've been assigned to.

527
00:23:05,950 --> 00:23:06,950
But if it is a woman,

528
00:23:06,950 --> 00:23:08,230
it'll likely be Judge Shu.

529
00:23:08,320 --> 00:23:09,880
She sees right through people.
She's reliable.

530
00:23:09,990 --> 00:23:11,080
He won't be able to fool her.

531
00:23:11,880 --> 00:23:12,670
Is this womanizer...

532
00:23:13,910 --> 00:23:15,630
What was the plaintiff's name again?

533
00:23:15,840 --> 00:23:17,520
- He Xiuguang.
- He Xiuguang.

534
00:23:17,950 --> 00:23:18,710
He Xiuguang.

535
00:23:19,080 --> 00:23:20,520
Don't worry, your mom won't fall for it.

536
00:23:21,430 --> 00:23:23,950
Wait, that's not the judge
you mentioned earlier.

537
00:23:24,280 --> 00:23:25,430
It was a three-character name.

538
00:23:25,430 --> 00:23:26,039
Right.

539
00:23:26,040 --> 00:23:27,120
Three characters.

540
00:23:27,120 --> 00:23:27,910
Ying Danian?

541
00:23:27,990 --> 00:23:28,800
No.

542
00:23:28,950 --> 00:23:30,840
The name was kind of a tongue-twister.

543
00:23:31,040 --> 00:23:32,080
I think the surname

544
00:23:32,910 --> 00:23:33,670
started with a Chen?

545
00:23:33,760 --> 00:23:34,670
No, it wasn't Chen.

546
00:23:34,760 --> 00:23:35,950
Actually, at Qingcheng Court,

547
00:23:35,950 --> 00:23:37,230
there aren't any judges named Chen.

548
00:23:37,280 --> 00:23:38,710
Hold on, let me double-check.

549
00:23:42,040 --> 00:23:42,990
Yeah, take a look.

550
00:23:45,390 --> 00:23:46,320
It's Shen.

551
00:23:46,880 --> 00:23:48,080
Shen Xie...

552
00:23:48,150 --> 00:23:50,040
- Shen Xiezhi. Yeah, that's the one.
- Right.

553
00:23:50,080 --> 00:23:51,150
Quite a mouthful.

554
00:23:51,800 --> 00:23:52,630
By the way,

555
00:23:53,950 --> 00:23:55,710
are you two close?

556
00:23:57,190 --> 00:23:58,080
Not really.

557
00:24:01,950 --> 00:24:03,120
We've met. I know him.

558
00:24:05,120 --> 00:24:05,760
Don't sweat it.

559
00:24:05,760 --> 00:24:07,320
He won't fall for He Xiuguang's tricks.

560
00:24:07,470 --> 00:24:08,990
Judges have seen it all.

561
00:24:11,390 --> 00:24:12,280
I hope you're right.

562
00:24:13,120 --> 00:24:14,710
Just hearing his name
makes my skin crawl.

563
00:24:23,230 --> 00:24:24,150
Good morning, Judge Shen.

564
00:24:25,120 --> 00:24:26,040
Judge Shen.

565
00:24:37,280 --> 00:24:40,240
(Courtroom 2: Shen Xiezhi,
Chen Xianghui, Qin Rui)

566
00:24:44,560 --> 00:24:46,520
(Family Court)

567
00:24:46,950 --> 00:24:48,390
I will now read the rules of the court.

568
00:24:48,910 --> 00:24:50,230
To maintain order

569
00:24:50,560 --> 00:24:52,520
and ensure the integrity
of these proceedings,

570
00:24:52,670 --> 00:24:54,230
per the Court Rules

571
00:24:54,230 --> 00:24:56,360
of the People's Republic of China,

572
00:24:56,600 --> 00:24:58,280
the following persons may not attend.

573
00:24:58,320 --> 00:24:59,760
One, minors,

574
00:25:00,190 --> 00:25:01,760
unless authorized by the court.

575
00:25:01,840 --> 00:25:04,230
Two, intoxicated
or mentally ill persons.

576
00:25:04,230 --> 00:25:06,390
Three, those deprived
of their political rights.

577
00:25:06,390 --> 00:25:08,080
All parties, participants,

578
00:25:08,080 --> 00:25:09,630
and spectators

579
00:25:09,630 --> 00:25:11,040
must adhere to the following.

580
00:25:11,280 --> 00:25:13,040
One, everyone present

581
00:25:13,040 --> 00:25:15,150
must follow the directions
of the Presiding Judge.

582
00:25:15,230 --> 00:25:15,800
Two,

583
00:25:15,800 --> 00:25:19,230
objections to the collegial panel or its members

584
00:25:19,230 --> 00:25:20,670
may not be raised during the hearing.

585
00:25:20,670 --> 00:25:21,280
Four,

586
00:25:21,280 --> 00:25:22,320
(Proof of Service. Long-term Civil Cases...)
do not move around the courtroom.

587
00:25:22,320 --> 00:25:23,910
Five, spectators are forbidden
from asking questions.

588
00:25:23,910 --> 00:25:25,120
Six, no applauding
or creating disturbances.

589
00:25:25,120 --> 00:25:26,470
(Litigation and Proof)
Seven, smoking is prohibited.

590
00:25:26,470 --> 00:25:26,880
Eight,

591
00:25:26,880 --> 00:25:27,600
before entering,

592
00:25:27,600 --> 00:25:29,520
all mobile devices must be switched off.

593
00:25:29,520 --> 00:25:32,230
Spectators with comments
regarding the proceedings

594
00:25:32,280 --> 00:25:33,230
may submit them in writing

595
00:25:33,230 --> 00:25:34,320
to the People's Court

596
00:25:34,320 --> 00:25:35,630
after the session has adjourned.

597
00:25:36,040 --> 00:25:37,360
The reading of the rules is complete.

598
00:25:37,470 --> 00:25:38,600
All rise.

599
00:25:38,910 --> 00:25:39,600
And now,

600
00:25:39,600 --> 00:25:41,190
please welcome the panel.

601
00:25:43,330 --> 00:25:45,680
♪Sweeping away the dust between us♪

602
00:25:45,710 --> 00:25:46,760
You may take a seat now.

603
00:25:46,910 --> 00:25:47,520
You may take a seat now.

604
00:25:47,520 --> 00:25:48,390
You may take a seat now.

605
00:25:48,390 --> 00:25:52,090
♪Searching for the warmth we had♪

606
00:25:52,440 --> 00:25:57,520
♪Like a migrating flock♪

607
00:26:03,950 --> 00:26:04,950
Judge Shu...

608
00:26:05,470 --> 00:26:06,390
Please, stay seated.

609
00:26:06,630 --> 00:26:07,630
Careful, you might fall.

610
00:26:07,630 --> 00:26:08,520
Thank you.

611
00:26:11,430 --> 00:26:12,150
Sit down.

612
00:26:16,320 --> 00:26:17,560
(Tianhai City People's Court)
Court is now in session.

613
00:26:17,560 --> 00:26:18,880
(In session)

614
00:26:18,880 --> 00:26:20,470
"Entering the gate of my longing,"

615
00:26:20,990 --> 00:26:23,150
"one learns of my sorrow's depth."

616
00:26:23,470 --> 00:26:26,230
(Defendant, Authorized Representative)
"Long is the longing, long is the memory."

617
00:26:26,710 --> 00:26:30,470
"Brief was the spark,
yet the yearning is infinite."

618
00:26:31,630 --> 00:26:33,950
Excuse me, Plaintiff.
My classical Chinese is a bit rusty.

619
00:26:34,040 --> 00:26:35,560
(Authorized Representative, Plaintiff)
Sorry, Your Honor.

620
00:26:35,800 --> 00:26:37,190
Let me put it in plain English.

621
00:26:39,630 --> 00:26:41,670
It was a bright spring day.

622
00:26:41,990 --> 00:26:43,150
Back then,

623
00:26:43,430 --> 00:26:45,280
I had truly hit rock bottom.

624
00:26:46,120 --> 00:26:48,390
The double blow
of losing my love and my career

625
00:26:48,880 --> 00:26:50,630
left me utterly hopeless.

626
00:26:50,990 --> 00:26:52,230
In fact,

627
00:26:53,520 --> 00:26:56,600
I had even begun
to contemplate ending it all.

628
00:26:57,040 --> 00:26:58,840
But I never could have imagined

629
00:26:58,990 --> 00:26:59,990
that the day

630
00:27:00,230 --> 00:27:02,990
would become
the luckiest day of my life.

631
00:27:02,990 --> 00:27:04,840
Because it was the day

632
00:27:05,320 --> 00:27:06,600
in the park

633
00:27:07,150 --> 00:27:08,390
when I met her.

634
00:27:10,040 --> 00:27:11,430
She was so delicate,

635
00:27:11,520 --> 00:27:12,840
so incredibly gentle.

636
00:27:13,080 --> 00:27:15,430
She just sat there,
listening to my grief,

637
00:27:15,470 --> 00:27:17,360
soothing my very soul.

638
00:27:18,760 --> 00:27:20,520
When I reached the most painful part,

639
00:27:21,880 --> 00:27:23,120
she held my hand.

640
00:27:23,600 --> 00:27:24,800
She felt so much for me,

641
00:27:25,190 --> 00:27:27,040
she was literally trembling.

642
00:27:28,950 --> 00:27:31,190
My mother had just
had surgery for a stroke.

643
00:27:31,360 --> 00:27:32,600
She was still in recovery!

644
00:27:38,470 --> 00:27:41,520
When I behold the violet past prime,

645
00:27:41,990 --> 00:27:43,280
and sable curls

646
00:27:43,800 --> 00:27:45,910
all silvered o'er with white,

647
00:27:46,560 --> 00:27:49,710
when lofty trees I see are

648
00:27:50,120 --> 00:27:51,390
barren of leaves.

649
00:27:52,190 --> 00:27:53,560
It only recently

650
00:27:53,600 --> 00:27:56,120
offered shade to the panting herd.

651
00:27:56,150 --> 00:27:57,080
Who are you calling names?

652
00:27:57,230 --> 00:27:58,120
Who's a herd?

653
00:27:58,360 --> 00:27:59,470
Summer's green,

654
00:27:59,470 --> 00:28:01,390
bundled up in sheaves,

655
00:28:01,990 --> 00:28:04,880
is carried away
like an old man to his grave.

656
00:28:05,120 --> 00:28:06,430
And so I must

657
00:28:06,430 --> 00:28:08,470
worry for your beauty.

658
00:28:08,880 --> 00:28:09,950
For one day

659
00:28:10,360 --> 00:28:12,470
you'll end up in the scrap heap of time.

660
00:28:12,520 --> 00:28:13,950
You're the piece of junk here!

661
00:28:14,230 --> 00:28:14,910
Calm down.

662
00:28:14,910 --> 00:28:15,630
My mom picked you up

663
00:28:15,630 --> 00:28:16,630
from the trash heap.

664
00:28:17,560 --> 00:28:18,470
Defendant,

665
00:28:18,710 --> 00:28:19,710
control yourself.

666
00:28:21,280 --> 00:28:22,120
Your Honor...

667
00:28:22,280 --> 00:28:23,320
How about Your Majesty?

668
00:28:23,520 --> 00:28:25,150
Speak like a normal person!

669
00:28:25,230 --> 00:28:26,430
Sun Daming!

670
00:28:29,840 --> 00:28:31,120
Ms. Qian, try to stay calm.

671
00:28:31,360 --> 00:28:33,280
Your children aren't
against you getting remarried.

672
00:28:33,470 --> 00:28:34,600
They just don't think

673
00:28:34,630 --> 00:28:36,150
Mr. He is the right choice for you.

674
00:28:36,710 --> 00:28:38,990
Why exactly am I not the right choice?

675
00:28:39,150 --> 00:28:40,360
Just because

676
00:28:40,560 --> 00:28:42,190
she's a little older than me?

677
00:28:42,230 --> 00:28:43,280
Twenty-three years.

678
00:28:43,430 --> 00:28:44,880
What's wrong with that gap?

679
00:28:44,990 --> 00:28:46,910
Does age really matter
when it comes to love?

680
00:28:47,670 --> 00:28:49,520
If an older man

681
00:28:49,520 --> 00:28:50,840
can be with a young woman

682
00:28:50,840 --> 00:28:52,710
and call it a perfect match,

683
00:28:52,710 --> 00:28:54,230
then why can't we?

684
00:28:54,470 --> 00:28:58,080
Or is it that it's only true love
when the man is older?

685
00:28:58,080 --> 00:28:59,670
Does the reverse not count?

686
00:29:00,390 --> 00:29:01,560
Now that you're older,

687
00:29:01,560 --> 00:29:02,760
do you think

688
00:29:02,800 --> 00:29:04,430
you're no longer worthy of being loved?

689
00:29:04,990 --> 00:29:07,120
If women keep
devaluing themselves like this,

690
00:29:07,230 --> 00:29:09,760
we'll never see true gender equality.

691
00:29:10,430 --> 00:29:12,120
Forget the mediation. We're done here.

692
00:29:12,190 --> 00:29:13,990
Look at her, she's been sobbing all day.

693
00:29:14,280 --> 00:29:15,150
Judge Shu,

694
00:29:15,230 --> 00:29:16,390
just give us a ruling already.

695
00:29:16,470 --> 00:29:18,280
Whatever you decide, we'll accept it.

696
00:29:18,470 --> 00:29:20,040
Exactly. Just rule on it.

697
00:29:20,120 --> 00:29:22,280
We're waiting for
the inheritance to be split

698
00:29:22,430 --> 00:29:24,430
so we can finally bury our father.

699
00:29:24,950 --> 00:29:26,190
We want to buy him a decent plot.

700
00:29:26,190 --> 00:29:28,560
It's the least we can do
to show our respect.

701
00:29:29,320 --> 00:29:31,430
Losing your father
has been devastating for you.

702
00:29:32,040 --> 00:29:33,470
But your own sister

703
00:29:33,470 --> 00:29:34,630
was seriously injured

704
00:29:34,710 --> 00:29:36,080
and is still in a wheelchair.

705
00:29:36,230 --> 00:29:38,040
Aren't you concerned about her future?

706
00:29:38,990 --> 00:29:40,910
That's a completely separate issue.

707
00:29:40,990 --> 00:29:42,360
Once the assets are divided,

708
00:29:43,150 --> 00:29:44,430
even if she

709
00:29:44,600 --> 00:29:46,080
hits rock bottom later on

710
00:29:46,150 --> 00:29:47,520
and comes to us for help,

711
00:29:47,840 --> 00:29:49,360
we won't just turn our backs on her.

712
00:29:49,360 --> 00:29:50,190
Right.

713
00:29:50,320 --> 00:29:51,990
But she has to take responsibility

714
00:29:52,150 --> 00:29:53,990
for the mistakes she made.

715
00:29:54,320 --> 00:29:57,190
A life for a life, a debt for a debt.

716
00:29:58,040 --> 00:29:58,910
You're a judge.

717
00:29:58,910 --> 00:30:01,710
I'm sure you see things
on a level we don't.

718
00:30:01,710 --> 00:30:05,190
We can't let family ties hijack the law.

719
00:30:05,430 --> 00:30:07,520
We shouldn't let sympathy
get in the way of justice.

720
00:30:07,520 --> 00:30:08,430
Don't you agree?

721
00:30:09,560 --> 00:30:10,470
Hold on.

722
00:30:10,950 --> 00:30:12,040
A life for a life?

723
00:30:12,390 --> 00:30:13,760
Who exactly are you accusing?

724
00:30:15,360 --> 00:30:16,280
Who else?

725
00:30:18,390 --> 00:30:19,320
Her.

726
00:30:20,520 --> 00:30:22,120
She's the one who killed my dad!

727
00:30:22,120 --> 00:30:23,080
Calm down.

728
00:30:28,430 --> 00:30:30,230
Look, as her brothers,

729
00:30:30,360 --> 00:30:32,470
it's not like we want to

730
00:30:32,990 --> 00:30:34,880
see her behind bars.

731
00:30:35,520 --> 00:30:36,990
But the fact remains that

732
00:30:36,990 --> 00:30:38,080
she's the reason Dad is dead.

733
00:30:38,950 --> 00:30:41,520
Dad's face was literally turning purple!

734
00:30:41,880 --> 00:30:45,120
I called for an ambulance.

735
00:30:45,120 --> 00:30:48,080
They told me
it'd take an hour to get there.

736
00:30:48,630 --> 00:30:51,150
Our road is so narrow that

737
00:30:51,150 --> 00:30:52,670
the vehicle couldn't
even reach the house.

738
00:30:52,670 --> 00:30:55,360
I panicked. I didn't know what to do.

739
00:30:55,360 --> 00:30:56,430
So what if it was an hour?

740
00:30:56,760 --> 00:30:58,280
You couldn't have just waited?

741
00:30:58,390 --> 00:30:59,430
If it was really too late,

742
00:30:59,430 --> 00:31:00,760
then it was just meant to be.

743
00:31:01,360 --> 00:31:02,390
If the ambulance was delayed,

744
00:31:02,390 --> 00:31:04,360
we could've sued
the emergency center for damages.

745
00:31:04,360 --> 00:31:05,990
A payout from a government agency?

746
00:31:05,990 --> 00:31:08,120
That wouldn't have been a small amount.

747
00:31:08,280 --> 00:31:09,390
It'd be over a million, right?

748
00:31:09,390 --> 00:31:10,280
Exactly.

749
00:31:10,360 --> 00:31:12,840
Leave professional matters
to the professionals.

750
00:31:13,320 --> 00:31:14,390
My wife is a nurse.

751
00:31:14,560 --> 00:31:15,630
She says if you don't know

752
00:31:15,710 --> 00:31:17,630
the extent of the injuries,

753
00:31:17,630 --> 00:31:19,910
you have to keep the person still.

754
00:31:20,190 --> 00:31:21,040
Just think.

755
00:31:21,120 --> 00:31:23,360
If you'd given him his meds

756
00:31:23,520 --> 00:31:25,080
and waited for help at home,

757
00:31:27,080 --> 00:31:28,360
our dear father

758
00:31:29,280 --> 00:31:31,760
wouldn't have been run over by a car!

759
00:31:34,040 --> 00:31:34,800
Unbelievable.

760
00:31:35,390 --> 00:31:36,630
The death certificate

761
00:31:36,630 --> 00:31:37,800
explicitly states

762
00:31:37,880 --> 00:31:39,670
that he died of sudden cardiac death.

763
00:31:39,880 --> 00:31:40,760
It was an illness.

764
00:31:40,910 --> 00:31:42,190
He didn't die from the accident.

765
00:31:44,800 --> 00:31:45,600
But...

766
00:31:45,600 --> 00:31:47,280
But my dad only died because her crash

767
00:31:47,280 --> 00:31:48,320
scared the life out of him!

768
00:31:48,520 --> 00:31:50,390
Exactly. She can't
just walk away from this.

769
00:31:50,390 --> 00:31:50,950
Not a chance.

770
00:31:50,950 --> 00:31:51,990
Am I right, Judge?

771
00:31:52,080 --> 00:31:52,990
If you still have

772
00:31:52,990 --> 00:31:54,320
objections regarding the liability

773
00:31:54,320 --> 00:31:55,320
or the cause of death,

774
00:31:55,320 --> 00:31:56,760
I suggest you call the police.

775
00:31:56,840 --> 00:31:58,520
Let them conduct a formal investigation.

776
00:31:58,630 --> 00:31:59,950
If it's a criminal matter,

777
00:32:00,080 --> 00:32:01,630
it will be moved
to the Criminal Division.

778
00:32:01,670 --> 00:32:03,120
As a Family Court judge,

779
00:32:03,120 --> 00:32:04,800
I have no jurisdiction
to settle that for you.

780
00:32:05,710 --> 00:32:07,710
Look, we aren't heartless.

781
00:32:07,710 --> 00:32:09,430
She is our sister, after all.

782
00:32:10,080 --> 00:32:11,230
You make it sound

783
00:32:11,470 --> 00:32:12,520
like we're desperate

784
00:32:12,630 --> 00:32:13,880
to throw her in prison.

785
00:32:13,880 --> 00:32:15,600
Exactly. There's no need for that.

786
00:32:16,710 --> 00:32:18,230
If there are no objections,

787
00:32:18,520 --> 00:32:19,280
we will proceed

788
00:32:19,280 --> 00:32:20,560
with the cause of death on record.

789
00:32:20,760 --> 00:32:22,150
But what about her neglect?

790
00:32:22,470 --> 00:32:23,280
Fine.

791
00:32:23,880 --> 00:32:26,120
Let's stick with sudden cardiac death.

792
00:32:27,950 --> 00:32:28,990
Mr. He,

793
00:32:28,990 --> 00:32:30,990
I truly admire your passion

794
00:32:31,120 --> 00:32:32,910
and your absolute devotion to love.

795
00:32:33,470 --> 00:32:35,390
But love and marriage are
two very different things.

796
00:32:35,630 --> 00:32:36,600
Love

797
00:32:36,670 --> 00:32:38,910
can be a sudden, impulsive rush.

798
00:32:39,120 --> 00:32:40,230
But marriage cannot.

799
00:32:40,560 --> 00:32:42,040
Marriage is about the daily grind,

800
00:32:42,190 --> 00:32:43,430
the chores, and the bills.

801
00:32:43,600 --> 00:32:45,840
It requires shared values
and compatibility.

802
00:32:46,280 --> 00:32:48,040
But from what we've gathered,

803
00:32:48,470 --> 00:32:49,670
you have no stable job,

804
00:32:50,040 --> 00:32:51,150
no permanent residence,

805
00:32:51,470 --> 00:32:53,080
and certainly no steady income.

806
00:32:53,390 --> 00:32:54,430
Ms. Qin,

807
00:32:54,840 --> 00:32:55,520
are these

808
00:32:55,520 --> 00:32:57,710
mainstream marriage values?

809
00:32:57,880 --> 00:32:59,910
Your thinking is so traditional.

810
00:33:00,120 --> 00:33:01,600
They are ancient and rigid.

811
00:33:01,710 --> 00:33:02,990
Have you really never

812
00:33:02,990 --> 00:33:05,430
experienced a love
worth risking everything for?

813
00:33:06,360 --> 00:33:08,230
If so, I honestly feel sorry for you.

814
00:33:08,880 --> 00:33:10,470
When true love finds you,

815
00:33:10,760 --> 00:33:12,280
it leaves you breathless.

816
00:33:12,430 --> 00:33:13,990
It leaves you completely distracted.

817
00:33:14,150 --> 00:33:15,710
Even a single day apart

818
00:33:15,910 --> 00:33:17,190
makes you lose your appetite.

819
00:33:17,800 --> 00:33:19,120
For her sake,

820
00:33:19,840 --> 00:33:21,800
you no longer fear aging or death.

821
00:33:21,800 --> 00:33:24,280
For her, you'd take on the whole world.

822
00:33:27,320 --> 00:33:29,080
I don't blame you

823
00:33:29,470 --> 00:33:30,670
for questioning me.

824
00:33:30,670 --> 00:33:32,520
That's the tragedy of your own lives.

825
00:33:33,080 --> 00:33:34,670
Because you've never experienced

826
00:33:34,710 --> 00:33:36,910
how sacred and beautiful
a love like this can be.

827
00:33:37,150 --> 00:33:38,230
You've never tasted

828
00:33:38,230 --> 00:33:39,840
fate's sweetest nectar.

829
00:33:40,520 --> 00:33:41,710
I can't take this anymore.

830
00:33:42,360 --> 00:33:43,390
This is disgusting.

831
00:33:46,080 --> 00:33:46,800
Judge,

832
00:33:46,990 --> 00:33:48,990
didn't you say
you wanted to see evidence?

833
00:33:49,150 --> 00:33:50,190
I have one more piece here.

834
00:33:50,190 --> 00:33:51,230
Please, take a look.

835
00:33:52,710 --> 00:33:53,630
Sister,

836
00:33:53,950 --> 00:33:55,630
let's think back for a second.

837
00:33:56,430 --> 00:33:57,600
Three months ago,

838
00:33:57,800 --> 00:34:01,470
I told you to get a critical
illness policy for Dad.

839
00:34:02,120 --> 00:34:02,880
At the time,

840
00:34:02,880 --> 00:34:04,320
(Critical Illness Insurance Contract)
that agent, Mr. Zhao,

841
00:34:04,320 --> 00:34:06,080
came by the house several times.

842
00:34:06,520 --> 00:34:08,070
The paperwork was all filled out.

843
00:34:08,550 --> 00:34:10,430
Even you thought the price was fair.

844
00:34:10,760 --> 00:34:11,990
I left the purchase to you.

845
00:34:12,510 --> 00:34:13,880
I trusted you.

846
00:34:14,320 --> 00:34:15,840
Now, three months have passed,

847
00:34:15,990 --> 00:34:18,470
and Dad died from sudden cardiac death.

848
00:34:18,910 --> 00:34:20,590
The insurance company
should be paying out.

849
00:34:20,880 --> 00:34:21,640
I think it's time

850
00:34:21,640 --> 00:34:23,280
you gave us a real explanation.

851
00:34:25,590 --> 00:34:26,880
He is asking you a question.

852
00:34:27,590 --> 00:34:28,590
Speak up!

853
00:34:32,110 --> 00:34:32,950
I picked out a policy

854
00:34:32,950 --> 00:34:35,030
with 500,000 yuan
in coverage for Dad.

855
00:34:35,030 --> 00:34:35,950
(Chat History)

856
00:34:35,950 --> 00:34:37,320
Sudden cardiac death

857
00:34:37,760 --> 00:34:39,160
was definitely covered.

858
00:34:39,390 --> 00:34:40,320
Sister.

859
00:34:40,320 --> 00:34:41,720
That's 500,000 yuan!

860
00:34:42,240 --> 00:34:43,760
Because you were too cheap

861
00:34:43,760 --> 00:34:44,640
to pay the premium,

862
00:34:44,640 --> 00:34:46,280
we're out half a million!

863
00:34:46,360 --> 00:34:47,390
Do you even realize that?

864
00:34:48,840 --> 00:34:49,550
I...

865
00:34:50,110 --> 00:34:51,680
I just got busy and forgot.

866
00:34:51,680 --> 00:34:53,550
You're a housewife with no children.

867
00:34:53,880 --> 00:34:55,590
Your only duty
was taking care of Dad!

868
00:34:55,680 --> 00:34:56,720
So what have you been doing?

869
00:34:58,510 --> 00:35:00,030
Judge, you heard her yourself.

870
00:35:00,390 --> 00:35:01,760
She just admitted it.

871
00:35:03,030 --> 00:35:04,320
She forgot to pay.

872
00:35:04,550 --> 00:35:06,800
And now we're out 500,000 yuan
because of her.

873
00:35:07,070 --> 00:35:08,320
She has to compensate us for that.

874
00:35:09,030 --> 00:35:10,200
We aren't asking for much.

875
00:35:10,280 --> 00:35:11,320
That 500,000 yuan should be

876
00:35:11,510 --> 00:35:12,430
split three ways.

877
00:35:12,760 --> 00:35:14,110
I'll even round down the change.

878
00:35:14,510 --> 00:35:15,680
Just pay the two of us

879
00:35:15,880 --> 00:35:17,360
160,000 yuan each.

880
00:35:18,640 --> 00:35:20,110
Wait, I thought it was 300,000?

881
00:35:20,280 --> 00:35:20,800
That was

882
00:35:20,800 --> 00:35:22,760
for killing Dad in the accident.

883
00:35:26,800 --> 00:35:28,280
The Judge told me to drop that for now.

884
00:35:28,840 --> 00:35:29,990
Let's keep these issues separate.

885
00:35:30,070 --> 00:35:31,680
Did you or did you not
make a mistake here?

886
00:35:32,840 --> 00:35:34,800
You need to
take responsibility for this.

887
00:35:35,590 --> 00:35:37,680
Honestly, the money is the least of it.

888
00:35:38,470 --> 00:35:39,390
My brother and I

889
00:35:39,390 --> 00:35:41,200
haven't even made you
pay for Dad's life yet.

890
00:35:41,200 --> 00:35:41,990
Exactly.

891
00:35:41,990 --> 00:35:43,990
We didn't even get to say goodbye.

892
00:35:43,990 --> 00:35:44,840
Yeah.

893
00:35:47,160 --> 00:35:48,070
Wait a second.

894
00:35:48,840 --> 00:35:49,510
Look at this.

895
00:35:49,510 --> 00:35:50,420
(Coverage Scope)
Sudden cardiac death isn't

896
00:35:50,420 --> 00:35:51,840
listed under the coverage.

897
00:35:56,320 --> 00:35:57,510
Acute myocardial infarction

898
00:35:57,510 --> 00:35:59,760
isn't the same thing
as sudden cardiac death?

899
00:36:02,070 --> 00:36:02,990
Sorry to interrupt,

900
00:36:02,990 --> 00:36:03,950
but I should clarify.

901
00:36:03,950 --> 00:36:05,430
A friend of mine lost his father

902
00:36:05,620 --> 00:36:07,470
to sudden cardiac death as well.

903
00:36:07,640 --> 00:36:09,280
He had critical illness insurance too,

904
00:36:09,360 --> 00:36:11,110
but the company refused to pay.

905
00:36:11,430 --> 00:36:13,390
There are many triggers

906
00:36:13,390 --> 00:36:14,390
for sudden cardiac death,

907
00:36:14,640 --> 00:36:16,680
including myocardial infarction.

908
00:36:16,840 --> 00:36:18,390
So even if you'd bought the policy,

909
00:36:18,550 --> 00:36:19,760
it might not have paid out.

910
00:36:19,950 --> 00:36:20,910
Now hold on, young lady.

911
00:36:20,910 --> 00:36:22,110
Explain yourself.

912
00:36:22,280 --> 00:36:24,760
Just because
your friend's father got denied,

913
00:36:25,390 --> 00:36:27,510
what makes you think they'd deny my dad?

914
00:36:27,590 --> 00:36:28,800
I only said it was a possibility.

915
00:36:29,070 --> 00:36:30,950
Possibility?
Don't just make things up.

916
00:36:30,950 --> 00:36:31,950
There's an easy fix.

917
00:36:32,200 --> 00:36:33,800
We'll just order an autopsy.

918
00:36:33,880 --> 00:36:34,840
Lu Huilan,

919
00:36:35,110 --> 00:36:37,680
do you have the guts to let them
perform an autopsy on Dad?

920
00:36:38,430 --> 00:36:39,880
If the results come back

921
00:36:40,430 --> 00:36:41,360
and the insurance denies us,

922
00:36:41,840 --> 00:36:43,070
then we will drop this.

923
00:36:43,320 --> 00:36:44,110
But if

924
00:36:44,200 --> 00:36:46,160
it was covered under the policy,

925
00:36:46,320 --> 00:36:48,510
then we want that 500,000 yuan.

926
00:36:48,510 --> 00:36:50,160
- Not a penny less.
- You'll cough it all up.

927
00:36:50,200 --> 00:36:51,030
Do you accept it?

928
00:36:55,110 --> 00:36:56,030
Mr. He.

929
00:36:56,110 --> 00:36:57,760
Let's put the essence of love

930
00:36:58,160 --> 00:37:00,390
and the signals of its arrival
aside for a moment.

931
00:37:00,470 --> 00:37:02,470
These topics are far too grandiose.

932
00:37:03,030 --> 00:37:04,390
Let's discuss

933
00:37:04,590 --> 00:37:06,470
what you're actually after
in this relationship.

934
00:37:06,990 --> 00:37:09,240
Before you and your love showed up,

935
00:37:09,360 --> 00:37:11,240
Ms. Qian lived a blissful,

936
00:37:11,280 --> 00:37:13,360
harmonious life with her children.

937
00:37:13,680 --> 00:37:15,390
But since you arrived with this love,

938
00:37:15,760 --> 00:37:16,360
it's true

939
00:37:16,590 --> 00:37:18,510
that my clients were initially opposed.

940
00:37:18,760 --> 00:37:20,030
But as of now,

941
00:37:20,360 --> 00:37:21,950
they've consented to your marriage.

942
00:37:22,390 --> 00:37:23,240
They even let you

943
00:37:23,240 --> 00:37:25,550
move into Ms. Qian's apartment
within the Second Ring.

944
00:37:25,840 --> 00:37:27,880
Normally, you'd be satisfied

945
00:37:28,030 --> 00:37:29,950
and simply enjoy
the fruits of your relationship.

946
00:37:30,910 --> 00:37:32,280
So why did you

947
00:37:32,550 --> 00:37:35,110
pressure Ms. Qian to sue her children

948
00:37:35,430 --> 00:37:37,160
to revoke the deed to six properties?

949
00:37:38,760 --> 00:37:40,840
Mother only gave them those houses

950
00:37:40,840 --> 00:37:42,360
on one condition.

951
00:37:42,510 --> 00:37:44,240
They had to be filial.

952
00:37:44,240 --> 00:37:45,680
How have we not been filial?

953
00:37:46,280 --> 00:37:47,840
Mom, tell him!

954
00:37:51,200 --> 00:37:53,070
They interfered with her marriage,

955
00:37:53,240 --> 00:37:54,840
destroyed her happiness,

956
00:37:54,990 --> 00:37:56,430
and withheld her income.

957
00:37:56,590 --> 00:37:58,760
They constantly criticize
the man she loves,

958
00:37:59,360 --> 00:38:01,640
leaving her in tears day and night.

959
00:38:01,880 --> 00:38:03,280
They turned their backs on her.

960
00:38:03,470 --> 00:38:04,680
We're just returning the favor.

961
00:38:04,760 --> 00:38:05,640
Everything I do

962
00:38:05,640 --> 00:38:07,590
is purely to protect my darling.

963
00:38:08,640 --> 00:38:10,280
I don't have a selfish bone in my body.

964
00:38:12,880 --> 00:38:13,880
Ms. Qin,

965
00:38:14,280 --> 00:38:17,430
why do you always equate love with money?

966
00:38:17,720 --> 00:38:19,280
Do you really believe

967
00:38:19,510 --> 00:38:21,550
that people without money
aren't entitled to love?

968
00:38:22,240 --> 00:38:23,240
Mr. He,

969
00:38:23,550 --> 00:38:24,760
in my opinion,

970
00:38:24,760 --> 00:38:26,430
those who can't put bread on the table

971
00:38:26,680 --> 00:38:28,070
have no business talking about love.

972
00:38:28,550 --> 00:38:29,640
How hideous.

973
00:38:30,360 --> 00:38:31,390
How vulgar.

974
00:38:31,640 --> 00:38:32,640
How materialistic.

975
00:38:33,320 --> 00:38:35,590
Birds of a feather flock together.

976
00:38:36,430 --> 00:38:38,550
If a lawyer has such a hideous soul,

977
00:38:38,680 --> 00:38:40,200
her clients can't be much better.

978
00:38:40,200 --> 00:38:41,240
Say that again!

979
00:38:41,320 --> 00:38:42,160
Plaintiff.

980
00:38:42,320 --> 00:38:43,320
Watch your tone.

981
00:38:43,720 --> 00:38:44,760
No personal attacks.

982
00:38:45,590 --> 00:38:47,200
You're all still so young.

983
00:38:47,320 --> 00:38:48,840
If you had the perspective

984
00:38:48,840 --> 00:38:50,800
that comes with age, you'd understand.

985
00:38:51,200 --> 00:38:53,070
There's always more money to be made,

986
00:38:53,320 --> 00:38:55,030
and another ladder to climb.

987
00:38:55,320 --> 00:38:57,720
The hurdles of reality never end.

988
00:38:57,840 --> 00:38:59,880
But life is fleeting.

989
00:39:00,470 --> 00:39:02,030
In this short existence,

990
00:39:02,390 --> 00:39:03,360
love

991
00:39:03,910 --> 00:39:05,550
might be a fleeting moment,

992
00:39:05,800 --> 00:39:08,320
a mere drop in the vast ocean.

993
00:39:08,320 --> 00:39:10,110
If you don't seize it,

994
00:39:10,240 --> 00:39:11,880
it's gone forever.

995
00:39:12,590 --> 00:39:14,880
Even if you're drowning
in wealth one day,

996
00:39:15,550 --> 00:39:16,880
what's the point?

997
00:39:19,840 --> 00:39:21,990
Am I right, Judge Shen?

998
00:39:24,160 --> 00:39:25,200
So, tell me.

999
00:39:25,360 --> 00:39:26,910
What did Guixiang and I do wrong?

1000
00:39:27,240 --> 00:39:28,990
We just chose to be brave

1001
00:39:28,990 --> 00:39:31,470
and give love everything we had.

1002
00:39:31,470 --> 00:39:33,510
In this dry, empty life,

1003
00:39:33,950 --> 00:39:34,390
when you

1004
00:39:34,390 --> 00:39:36,470
find a soulmate like Guixiang,

1005
00:39:37,160 --> 00:39:38,470
would you really walk away?

1006
00:39:40,200 --> 00:39:42,030
If you were drowning in darkness

1007
00:39:42,030 --> 00:39:43,360
and saw a ray of light,

1008
00:39:44,110 --> 00:39:45,990
wouldn't you reach for it?

1009
00:39:49,030 --> 00:39:50,200
If you knew

1010
00:39:50,200 --> 00:39:51,360
that letting her go meant

1011
00:39:51,360 --> 00:39:54,070
never feeling that spark again,

1012
00:39:54,280 --> 00:39:56,070
could you still turn your back on her?

1013
00:39:56,240 --> 00:39:57,470
Would any of you?

1014
00:39:58,590 --> 00:39:59,590
Could you?

1015
00:40:24,390 --> 00:40:25,320
Ms. Qin,

1016
00:40:25,720 --> 00:40:27,550
why do you always equate love

1017
00:40:27,550 --> 00:40:28,910
with money?

1018
00:40:29,200 --> 00:40:30,720
Do you really believe

1019
00:40:30,990 --> 00:40:32,990
that people without money
aren't entitled to love?

1020
00:40:40,430 --> 00:40:42,430
(There's always more money to be made,)

1021
00:40:42,640 --> 00:40:44,200
(and another ladder to climb.)

1022
00:40:44,280 --> 00:40:46,720
The hurdles of reality never end.

1023
00:40:46,720 --> 00:40:48,840
But life is fleeting.

1024
00:40:48,910 --> 00:40:50,640
In this short existence,

1025
00:40:50,640 --> 00:40:53,390
love might be a fleeting moment,

1026
00:40:53,680 --> 00:40:56,160
a mere drop in the vast ocean.

1027
00:40:56,240 --> 00:40:57,840
If you don't seize it,

1028
00:40:57,990 --> 00:40:59,510
it's gone forever.

1029
00:41:09,160 --> 00:41:10,030
Come in.

1030
00:41:10,550 --> 00:41:11,720
Oh my goodness.

1031
00:41:12,320 --> 00:41:13,510
It never ends.

1032
00:41:13,910 --> 00:41:15,070
What happened now?

1033
00:41:15,360 --> 00:41:16,680
The same two mama's boys.

1034
00:41:16,760 --> 00:41:17,840
Who else?

1035
00:41:18,360 --> 00:41:19,910
I seriously don't get it.

1036
00:41:20,030 --> 00:41:21,590
They can barely take care of themselves.

1037
00:41:21,590 --> 00:41:23,200
Why on earth do they have to have kids?

1038
00:41:23,800 --> 00:41:25,470
And both sets of parents too.

1039
00:41:25,720 --> 00:41:26,910
They've failed one generation.

1040
00:41:26,910 --> 00:41:28,390
Why are they so eager

1041
00:41:28,390 --> 00:41:29,680
to mess up the next one?

1042
00:41:29,840 --> 00:41:31,110
In that whole family,

1043
00:41:31,110 --> 00:41:32,430
excluding the baby in diapers

1044
00:41:32,430 --> 00:41:33,240
in the stroller,

1045
00:41:33,240 --> 00:41:34,760
not a single person is sane.

1046
00:41:35,030 --> 00:41:35,990
Do you know how badly

1047
00:41:35,990 --> 00:41:37,550
I wanted to scream at them today?

1048
00:41:37,550 --> 00:41:39,990
"I'm begging you,
leave the child out of this!"

1049
00:41:40,070 --> 00:41:41,240
If you can't raise them,

1050
00:41:41,240 --> 00:41:42,880
at least take some responsibility

1051
00:41:42,880 --> 00:41:44,240
once they're here.

1052
00:41:44,240 --> 00:41:45,110
Can't they just learn?

1053
00:41:45,110 --> 00:41:45,910
Honestly,

1054
00:41:46,070 --> 00:41:47,160
I'm so fed up!

1055
00:41:54,590 --> 00:41:55,510
I feel much better now.

1056
00:41:59,110 --> 00:41:59,880
Jing,

1057
00:42:00,550 --> 00:42:02,070
how are things with Yongjiu?

1058
00:42:02,910 --> 00:42:04,070
What do you mean?

1059
00:42:04,320 --> 00:42:05,360
About having a second kid.

1060
00:42:06,800 --> 00:42:08,680
When did I ever say
I wanted another one?

1061
00:42:08,680 --> 00:42:10,550
Well, you're burning
the calories anyway.

1062
00:42:10,550 --> 00:42:12,070
Might as well get a baby out of it.

1063
00:42:13,030 --> 00:42:14,950
A happy couple like you should

1064
00:42:14,950 --> 00:42:16,320
do your part for society.

1065
00:42:16,590 --> 00:42:17,760
We aren't burning any.

1066
00:42:19,430 --> 00:42:20,160
None.

1067
00:42:21,160 --> 00:42:22,280
What do you mean by that?

1068
00:42:25,880 --> 00:42:27,110
He isn't in the mood.

1069
00:42:28,200 --> 00:42:30,200
Maybe it's just our age.
It didn't happen.

1070
00:42:30,640 --> 00:42:32,640
That's nonsense. You aren't old at all.

1071
00:42:34,880 --> 00:42:36,110
This definitely isn't normal.

1072
00:42:36,720 --> 00:42:37,640
Jing,

1073
00:42:38,240 --> 00:42:38,880
if I were you,

1074
00:42:38,880 --> 00:42:40,840
I'd take him to see a doctor.

1075
00:42:40,990 --> 00:42:41,760
You know,

1076
00:42:41,760 --> 00:42:42,950
even just some medicine

1077
00:42:43,030 --> 00:42:44,720
to get things back on track.

1078
00:42:46,430 --> 00:42:47,430
Never mind.

1079
00:42:47,840 --> 00:42:48,720
Come on.

1080
00:42:54,720 --> 00:42:55,760
Fei's class is almost over.

1081
00:42:56,160 --> 00:42:57,030
I have to pick her up.

1082
00:42:57,110 --> 00:42:58,200
I'll come with you.

1083
00:42:58,590 --> 00:42:59,720
What for?

1084
00:43:00,240 --> 00:43:01,800
I'm taking her home with me today.

1085
00:43:14,620 --> 00:43:18,080
♪All the little things
between you and me♪

1086
00:43:18,080 --> 00:43:20,760
♪Woven into our lives♪

1087
00:43:21,610 --> 00:43:23,590
♪The building blocks of life♪

1088
00:43:23,590 --> 00:43:25,290
♪Shape the sky above us♪

1089
00:43:25,290 --> 00:43:27,450
♪Are you doing alright?♪

1090
00:43:27,770 --> 00:43:30,450
♪What are you struggling for?♪

1091
00:43:31,330 --> 00:43:35,150
♪Some questions weigh like mountains♪

1092
00:43:35,530 --> 00:43:40,380
♪How do we piece life back together?♪

1093
00:43:40,940 --> 00:43:45,130
♪So hate can fade
and love feels new again♪

1094
00:43:45,130 --> 00:43:48,200
♪Reclaim the barren parts of life♪

1095
00:43:48,200 --> 00:43:54,570
♪Walking this road
together, still hoping♪

1096
00:43:55,360 --> 00:44:00,420
♪Let me be the wind at dawn♪

1097
00:44:00,720 --> 00:44:04,690
♪Blowing away all the pain♪

1098
00:44:04,920 --> 00:44:09,900
♪Let me be the balance
that holds the weight♪

1099
00:44:10,320 --> 00:44:14,880
♪Where fairness stands♪

1100
00:44:15,350 --> 00:44:17,590
♪Within every heart♪

1101
00:44:17,590 --> 00:44:20,240
♪So many voices calling♪

1102
00:44:20,500 --> 00:44:24,790
♪Struggling, lost,
waiting for an answer♪

1103
00:44:24,790 --> 00:44:27,140
♪Light up the lamps♪

1104
00:44:27,140 --> 00:44:29,810
♪To answer those voices♪

1105
00:44:30,120 --> 00:44:32,240
♪You deserve to be happy♪

1106
00:44:32,240 --> 00:44:34,990
♪Loud and clear♪

1107
00:44:34,990 --> 00:44:37,310
♪All the little things♪

1108
00:44:37,310 --> 00:44:40,010
♪Woven into our lives♪

1109
00:44:40,830 --> 00:44:42,880
♪The building blocks of life♪

1110
00:44:42,880 --> 00:44:44,590
♪Shape the sky above us♪

1111
00:44:44,590 --> 00:44:47,040
♪Are you doing alright?♪

1112
00:44:47,040 --> 00:44:49,150
♪What are you struggling for?♪

1113
00:44:49,400 --> 00:44:51,530
♪Some questions♪

1114
00:44:52,100 --> 00:44:54,800
♪Weigh like mountains♪

1115
00:44:57,690 --> 00:45:02,840
♪Let me be the wind at dawn♪

1116
00:45:03,120 --> 00:45:07,130
♪Blowing away all the pain♪

1117
00:45:07,310 --> 00:45:12,360
♪Let me be the balance
that holds the weight♪

1118
00:45:12,730 --> 00:45:16,430
♪Where fairness stands♪

1119
00:45:16,600 --> 00:45:19,680
♪Within the law♪

1120
00:45:20,840 --> 00:45:29,520
♪And within every heart♪
